---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is KY a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (9 Points)"
  description="KY is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth 9 points (K=5, Y=4), KY means cattle in Scottish dialect. The second-highest SOWPODS-only 2-letter word after ZE."
  keywords="is ky a scrabble word, ky scrabble valid, ky sowpods only, ky scottish cattle, ky 9 points scrabble, high scoring two letter words sowpods"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is KY a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (9 Points)",
    "description": "KY is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth 9 points, KY means cattle in Scottish dialect.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ky-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is KY a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "KY is valid ONLY in SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). It is NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List) used in North American play. At 9 points, it's the second-highest SOWPODS-only 2-letter word after ZE (11pts)." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does KY mean?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "KY (also spelled KYE) means cattle in Scottish dialect. It's a plural noun referring to cows. Collins accepted it as a valid English word used in Scottish and Northern English dialects." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is KY worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "KY is worth 9 points: K(5) + Y(4) = 9. This makes it one of the highest-scoring two-letter words in SOWPODS, beaten only by ZE (11pts) and ZO (11pts)." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is KY a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">KY — a Scottish word for cattle — is one of the most powerful two-letter words exclusive to SOWPODS. At 9 points, it's the second-highest scoring SOWPODS-only two-letter word (behind ZE at 11 points). If you're playing in an international tournament or Collins-based game, KY is a devastating play. In TWL? It'll cost you your turn.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-orange-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-950/30 to-amber-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-orange-500/70">⚠ SOWPODS Only</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">KY</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-orange-300 font-semibold mb-3">9 points · K(5) + Y(4) · Scottish: cattle · SOWPODS only</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">KY is valid in Collins (international) but INVALID in TWL (North America). At 9 points with no vowels, it's a devastating consonant-only play in SOWPODS games.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-orange-500/30 bg-orange-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">✗</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Invalid TWL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">✓</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">#2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SOWPODS-Only Rank</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Does KY Mean?</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📖 Definition</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">KY (also written KYE) is a <span class="text-white font-medium">Scottish/Northern English dialectal word meaning cattle or cows</span>. It's the plural form used in rural Scotland — "The ky are in the field." Collins includes many dialect words that TWL considers too regional.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">SOWPODS-Only 2-Letter Word Rankings</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZE</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">11pts #1</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZO</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">11pts #1</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KY</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9pts #2 ★</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FY</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">8pts #3</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CH</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">7pts #4</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dictionary Status</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10"><p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ INVALID in TWL (NASPA)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Not in Tournament Word List. Playing KY in North American tournaments loses your turn. NASPA doesn't include Scottish dialect words.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Valid in SOWPODS (Collins)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Accepted in Collins Scrabble Words. Legal in international tournaments, UK/Australian clubs, and Collins-based online games. A highly prized play.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Play KY</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">K-tile rescue:</span> K(5) is hard to use — few words start or end with K in short forms. KY gives your K tile a 9-point exit without needing a vowel.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium devastation:</span> K on a double-letter = 14pts. Y on a double-letter = 13pts. KY on a double-word = 18pts! That's QI-level scoring from common tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Consonant-heavy relief:</span> Both K and Y are consonants (Y serving as vowel sound). KY clears two tricky consonants while scoring 9 — your rack will thank you.</p></div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ya-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is YA a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-zo-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is ZO a Scrabble Word? The Highest SOWPODS-Only Play</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word's validity instantly — free, realtime, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
